Defendant Varnell  Taylor in court, in custody, with attorney Robert J. Penegor.   Kevin M. Osborne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Plea Colloquy

Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

12 months Jail (Credit - 152 days)

Term of Probation: 2 Years

Conditions of Probation:
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Perform  20 hours of community service each year of probation with the 20 hours in the second year to be completed by December 15, 2016.
- Obtain a valid license within 60 days;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Take a victim impact/empathy course;
- No contact with co-defendants, victim and 2310 Hillsdale Drive East or it's residents.
- Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge

Restitution: $600.00  to Lisa L.(to be paid $50.00 per month commencing 4-1-15)

Costs: $278.00 
DNA Surcharge:  $250.00
(To be paid as a condition of probation after restitution is paid.)

Condition Time: 60 days Jail - Stayed and to be used at the agent's discretion.

Felony warnings, immigration warnings,  voting rights and firearms warnings given.
